WEBVTT

00:03.210 --> 00:05.830
[ Monitor beeping ]

00:11.750 --> 00:15.500
Meredith:
There's a saying we hear
a lot around hospitals...

00:15.500 --> 00:18.290
that goes like this --

00:18.290 --> 00:22.040
"Pain is inevitable.
Suffering is optional."

00:23.750 --> 00:24.960
It didn't work.

00:24.960 --> 00:26.670
But I doubt the person
who coined it

00:26.670 --> 00:28.460
ever went through
major surgery.

00:28.460 --> 00:31.290
[ Sobbing ]
It didn't work.

00:31.290 --> 00:33.290
[ Sobbing ]

00:33.290 --> 00:34.620
[ Glass shattering ]

00:34.620 --> 00:36.460
Or maybe they didn't mean
physical pain.

00:36.460 --> 00:37.880
Maybe they meant
the other kind --

00:37.880 --> 00:39.460
the worse kind.

00:39.460 --> 00:41.040
[ Glass shattering ]

00:41.040 --> 00:42.960
Is Meredith in there?
Yes.

00:42.960 --> 00:45.080
[ Glass shattering ]

00:45.080 --> 00:46.420
I'm gonna go
talk to her.

00:46.420 --> 00:49.170
Uh...
Not a good idea, all right?

00:49.170 --> 00:53.170
Okay, right now she looks
and sounds just like her mother.

00:53.170 --> 00:55.210
Okay? I mean,
best we just lay low,

00:55.210 --> 00:56.250
let her work this out
herself.

00:56.250 --> 00:59.750
Believe me. I had to
learn it the hard way.

00:59.750 --> 01:02.080
-With Ellis?
-Both of them.

01:02.080 --> 01:05.040
[ Glass shattering ]
I think we should go in.

01:05.040 --> 01:07.540
Maybe they meant the kind
of searing, seething,

01:07.540 --> 01:10.210
boiling pain that tells you
you're a failure and a fraud.

01:10.210 --> 01:13.040
[ Clattering ]

01:17.500 --> 01:20.250
Well, I hope you don't
want any coffee, 'cause
I broke all the mugs.

01:20.250 --> 01:24.080
"Suffering is optional."

01:24.080 --> 01:26.830
That person didn't know what
the...they were talking about.

01:33.380 --> 01:35.330
[ Arguing in Italian ]

01:38.880 --> 01:42.000
Excuse me. Scusi!

01:42.000 --> 01:43.920
Sorry. That's the only word
I know in Italian.

01:43.920 --> 01:46.460
Um, why are we
speaking Italian?

01:46.460 --> 01:48.000
He's my stupid
little brother.

01:48.000 --> 01:51.920
[ Both speaking Italian ]

01:51.920 --> 01:54.920
[ Sighs ]

01:54.920 --> 01:57.880
Um...hi.
Uh, excuse me.

01:57.880 --> 01:59.080
I'm still here!

01:59.080 --> 02:00.960
I-I still
don't speak Italian.

02:00.960 --> 02:02.460
You know what?
Have fun.

02:02.460 --> 02:04.250
I'm gonna sleep
at the hospital.

02:04.250 --> 02:06.420
Wha-- Ugh!
[ Door opens and closes ]

02:06.420 --> 02:08.330
Agh!
He's such a baby boy!

02:08.330 --> 02:09.960
Trying to pretend
like sex doesn't exist

02:09.960 --> 02:11.830
just because
he isn't having any.

02:11.830 --> 02:13.250
Andrew's Italian?

02:13.250 --> 02:14.920
Andrea is
his given name.

02:14.920 --> 02:16.000
Huh.

02:18.830 --> 02:20.210
Where were we?

02:20.210 --> 02:21.330
I think --
I'm pretty sure

02:21.330 --> 02:23.170
that you were about to
take off your shirt.

02:23.170 --> 02:25.080
I think so, too.
[ Chuckles ]

02:25.080 --> 02:28.250
♪♪

02:28.250 --> 02:31.500
[ Snoring ]

02:31.500 --> 02:35.290
♪♪

02:35.290 --> 02:37.460
[ Groans softly ]

02:37.460 --> 02:42.460
♪♪

02:42.460 --> 02:47.460
♪♪

02:47.460 --> 02:49.040
[ Lens shatters ]
[ Gasps ]

02:51.460 --> 02:52.960
[ Glass crinkling ]

02:52.960 --> 02:58.750
♪♪

02:58.750 --> 03:04.830
♪♪

03:04.830 --> 03:06.540
[ Softly ]
Oh, my God.

03:06.540 --> 03:10.210
♪♪

03:10.210 --> 03:12.250
[ Sighs ]
I'm sorry for Megan.

03:12.250 --> 03:13.540
But?

03:13.540 --> 03:14.920
But I'm so glad
she doesn't have to go

03:14.920 --> 03:17.380
back to Iraq right away.

03:17.380 --> 03:19.120
Is that awful?
Am I awful?

03:19.120 --> 03:21.330
Yeah. [ Laughs ]

03:21.330 --> 03:23.540
-Pretty awful.
-[ Chuckles ]

03:23.540 --> 03:27.420
♪♪

03:30.080 --> 03:31.670
You ready? Tuck's
gonna late if we don't --

03:31.670 --> 03:33.250
I don't want to.

03:33.250 --> 03:34.830
You don't want to ride
with me?

03:34.830 --> 03:39.040
I don't want to stuff my feet
into these shoes.

03:39.040 --> 03:40.750
You know, when Webber
became chief,

03:40.750 --> 03:43.960
he did not have to toddle around
on sticks all day.

03:43.960 --> 03:45.710
When Hunt became chief,

03:45.710 --> 03:48.580
he did not have to
squeeze five toes

03:48.580 --> 03:50.380
into a space
built for two.

03:50.380 --> 03:52.920
But I become chief
and I can't wear

03:52.920 --> 03:56.040
my perfectly comfortable
surgical clogs anymore.

03:56.040 --> 03:57.830
And you know why?

03:57.830 --> 04:00.120
-Society?
-S-- Society.

04:02.330 --> 04:04.580
[ Sighs ]

04:04.580 --> 04:05.790
Um...

04:05.790 --> 04:06.920
I'm comin'!

04:06.920 --> 04:08.580
Okay. [ Clears throat ]

04:10.880 --> 04:14.460
[ Birds chirping ]

04:14.460 --> 04:16.040
You sent the kids to school
and went back to bed?

04:16.040 --> 04:17.170
-Don't judge me.
-Don't judge her.

04:17.170 --> 04:19.960
I'm not. Look.
She'll heal, right?

04:19.960 --> 04:21.620
Eventually,
the wound will close.
It'll close.

04:21.620 --> 04:23.420
Yeah, it'll be ugly
and painful.

04:23.420 --> 04:25.540
Probably worse
than it was before.

04:25.540 --> 04:27.380
And it'll take months to heal.
She won't be able to travel.

04:27.380 --> 04:29.830
But it will close.

04:29.830 --> 04:32.420
You'll use mesh, and it'll
take time, but it will close.

04:32.420 --> 04:34.290
And now she has a functioning
bowel, which she ---

04:34.290 --> 04:35.290
-Stop!
-You mad at yourself?

04:35.290 --> 04:36.540
Think you were
wrong to try?

04:36.540 --> 04:39.000
Yeah, I'm mad at myself.
I was overconfident.

04:39.000 --> 04:40.500
And I'm also mad
at medicine.

04:40.500 --> 04:42.330
Fair enough, but don't
take it out on the wall.

04:42.330 --> 04:44.290
Well, you did a terrible job
patching it.

04:44.290 --> 04:45.500
You can see
the whole entire outline.

04:45.500 --> 04:47.080
All right, well,
just stop picking at it

04:47.080 --> 04:49.250
before we have to replace
the whole damn thing.

04:54.250 --> 04:55.750
Alex.
Hmm?

04:55.750 --> 04:57.920
That's it.

04:57.920 --> 04:59.170
That's it!

05:01.250 --> 05:02.420
[ Door closes ]

05:02.420 --> 05:04.380
-Meredith?
-Not till everyone gets here.

05:04.380 --> 05:07.080
Till --
Okay, who's everyone?

05:07.080 --> 05:08.750
I got your text.

05:08.750 --> 05:09.920
Dr. Altman.

05:09.920 --> 05:11.880
An abdominal-wall
transplant.

05:11.880 --> 05:13.670
[ Beeping ]

05:13.670 --> 05:15.920
I want to do an abdominal-wall
transplant on Megan Hunt.

05:15.920 --> 05:17.880
I want to harvest the skin,
the musculature,

05:17.880 --> 05:19.790
and the fascia
from a donor.

05:19.790 --> 05:22.540
This surgery has been
done three times before,
twice successfully.

05:22.540 --> 05:24.120
But they were done

05:24.120 --> 05:27.170
with a simultaneous
small-bowel transplant.

05:27.170 --> 05:29.750
So this is easier because we've
already repaired her bowel.

05:29.750 --> 05:32.620
And I would use a bone graft
to limit our risk of rejection.

05:32.620 --> 05:34.500
I mean, we keep trying
to fix this thing,

05:34.500 --> 05:37.080
and the more we try to fix it,
the worse it gets.

05:37.080 --> 05:39.620
So why do we keep
trying to fix it?

05:39.620 --> 05:41.540
Let's just replace it.

05:41.540 --> 05:43.290
All right, well,
what do you need from us?

05:43.290 --> 05:45.420
Well, I need your approval,
and I need you to back me up

05:45.420 --> 05:47.460
in case she doesn't
give me her approval.

05:47.460 --> 05:49.830
And I need you here
as Megan Hunt's advocate.

05:49.830 --> 05:53.420
I know you think I overstepped
by taking on this case.

05:53.420 --> 05:56.540
But I am able to separate the
personal and the professional.

05:56.540 --> 05:58.500
And if we do this,
I want you to scrub in.

05:58.500 --> 06:01.290
I don't want anyone
questioning my motives
from this point forward.

06:01.290 --> 06:04.460
So if we're gonna do this,
if we're gonna pull this off,

06:04.460 --> 06:06.460
I need everybody on board.

06:06.460 --> 06:12.080
♪♪

06:19.250 --> 06:21.120
Jackson:
Hey, you left early.

06:21.120 --> 06:23.420
-Yeah, busy day.
-Yeah, well, Maggie said a thing

06:23.420 --> 06:25.290
about a thing you
apparently said to Maggie?

06:25.290 --> 06:26.540
Hey, you know what?
My day is full.

06:26.540 --> 06:28.250
Can you take her
to daycare?

06:28.250 --> 06:30.920
-Ah. Hey.
-Okay. Bye.

06:30.920 --> 06:32.920
Uh --

06:32.920 --> 06:35.540
Well, do you think
that Mommy's avoiding me?

06:35.540 --> 06:38.420
I think Mommy's definitely
avoiding Daddy, don't you?

06:38.420 --> 06:40.210
[ Cellphone clicking ]

06:40.210 --> 06:42.960
[ Breathlessly ]
Um, I did a thing.

06:42.960 --> 06:44.670
A stupid thing.

06:44.670 --> 06:46.380
And I know that you don't want
to be my new Stephanie,

06:46.380 --> 06:48.620
but until I find
a new Stephanie, you're it.

06:48.620 --> 06:50.170
You're who
I've got to talk to.

06:50.170 --> 06:52.330
And I need you to tell me
exactly how to fix

06:52.330 --> 06:54.290
this incredibly
stupid thing!

06:54.290 --> 06:56.040
W-W-W-What the hell
did you do?

06:56.040 --> 06:59.250
Levi:
Hey. There. Hi.

06:59.250 --> 07:00.790
That. I did that.

07:00.790 --> 07:02.420
[ Whispering ]
You left your I.D.,

07:02.420 --> 07:05.540
which I figured
you probably need.

07:05.540 --> 07:07.960
My mom found it,
which was...awkward.

07:07.960 --> 07:09.380
That was
your mom's house?

07:09.380 --> 07:11.790
Livin' at home,
you know.

07:11.790 --> 07:13.830
'Cause costs are high.

07:13.830 --> 07:16.040
So, anyway...

07:16.040 --> 07:17.710
see you later,
hopefully.

07:17.710 --> 07:22.290
♪♪

07:22.290 --> 07:23.460
You slept with him?

07:23.460 --> 07:25.580
No. No.
I did not sleep.

07:25.580 --> 07:28.040
I had sex with him,
and then I left!

07:28.040 --> 07:29.670
Alex:
You slept with Glasses?

07:29.670 --> 07:35.290
♪♪

07:35.290 --> 07:38.170
[ Laughs ]
Oh, God.

07:38.170 --> 07:39.960
[ Laughing ] Oh, wow!

07:39.960 --> 07:42.620
I mean, that's just --
That's -- Wow.

07:42.620 --> 07:46.460
[ Laughing ]

07:46.460 --> 07:48.120
I want to laugh, too,

07:48.120 --> 07:50.040
but I'm trying so hard
to be polite.

07:50.040 --> 07:52.080
What would
Stephanie do?

07:54.710 --> 07:57.080
This is a donor abdomen?

07:57.080 --> 07:59.880
Yes, we would use
the abdominal skin,

07:59.880 --> 08:01.710
the musculature,
the fascia

08:01.710 --> 08:04.040
the same way we would
from a donor kidney.

08:04.040 --> 08:06.540
This is groundbreaking.

08:06.540 --> 08:09.170
You know we see a lot of
soldiers with Megan's injury.

08:09.170 --> 08:11.920
If she can pull this off,
it can change a lot of lives.

08:11.920 --> 08:14.080
If it works,
I'll have full function?

08:14.080 --> 08:15.880
-Motor and sensory?
-Yes.

08:15.880 --> 08:18.790
And the recovery?
Should be a few weeks,
not a few months.

08:18.790 --> 08:21.000
-But what if it doesn't work?
-Mom!

08:21.000 --> 08:22.500
I don't like this,
Megan.

08:22.500 --> 08:24.000
-I don't like it, either.
-No one asked you.

08:24.000 --> 08:25.420
Megan,
they're just worried.

08:25.420 --> 08:26.710
No, they just want me
stuck here.

08:26.710 --> 08:28.120
Because they just
got you back!

08:28.120 --> 08:30.880
-They're scared.
-Yeah, well, so am I!

08:30.880 --> 08:32.880
You know what else I am?

08:32.880 --> 08:34.920
In pain.

08:34.920 --> 08:38.670
[ Monitor beeping ]

08:38.670 --> 08:40.960
I make a lot of jokes, and
I'm addicted to silver linings

08:40.960 --> 08:44.000
because jokes and silver linings
kept me alive.

08:44.000 --> 08:46.290
But...

08:46.290 --> 08:49.210
I was a hostage.

08:49.210 --> 08:50.960
And now, without this,
I'm a hostage again.

08:50.960 --> 08:53.380
To this bed. To this wound.

08:53.380 --> 08:55.080
And she has a plan
to set me free.

08:55.080 --> 08:57.790
And just to be clear,
I don't have to be
the one who does this.

08:57.790 --> 09:00.170
If you feel more comfortable
with Dr. Bailey or Dr. Webber,

09:00.170 --> 09:03.960
that's completely fine
with me.

09:03.960 --> 09:05.960
You are my surgeon,
Dr. Grey.

09:07.580 --> 09:11.330
Just...promise me that you'll
find me a killer set of abs.

09:17.750 --> 09:19.790
I'm gonna need your Sub-I's
to help me find that donor.

09:19.790 --> 09:22.210
Uh, I can all but assure you
they'll screw up,

09:22.210 --> 09:23.460
but you can try.

09:23.460 --> 09:25.920
You think I can do this?

09:25.920 --> 09:28.880
Yes.
I think you can do this.

09:28.880 --> 09:32.460
♪♪

09:32.460 --> 09:34.040
♪ Tell me something
I don't know ♪

09:34.040 --> 09:36.040
That 180 from
the depths of despair

09:36.040 --> 09:38.170
to the
revolutionary solution?

09:38.170 --> 09:39.620
That's impressive.

09:39.620 --> 09:42.080
Yep.
That's pure Ellis, too.

09:42.080 --> 09:44.000
♪ 'Cause I'm movin' on ♪

09:44.000 --> 09:45.580
-Hi.
-Hey!

09:45.580 --> 09:47.460
Uh, I mean...hello.
[ Clears throat ]

09:47.460 --> 09:51.380
Uh, yeah. You know what?
I'm sorry. I got to, um...

09:51.380 --> 09:53.250
Thank you.

09:53.250 --> 09:54.620
♪ Ooh-ooh, ooh-ooh ♪

09:54.620 --> 09:57.000
Meredith: The patient is
a 36-year-old Caucasian woman

09:57.000 --> 09:58.670
of Scottish descent,

09:58.670 --> 10:01.620
so we're looking for skin
that's more peach than olive.

10:01.620 --> 10:03.380
Is complexion important?

10:03.380 --> 10:06.170
If you were gonna replace
a big chunk of your body

10:06.170 --> 10:08.380
with a big chunk
of someone else's body,

10:08.380 --> 10:09.580
wouldn't you want
the parts to match?

10:09.580 --> 10:11.120
Shouldn't you
just call UNOS?

10:11.120 --> 10:13.540
We've tried that. There are
no pending donors that match.

10:13.540 --> 10:14.920
This is where
you come in.

10:14.920 --> 10:17.330
We want you to scour ERs,
chase ambulances --

10:17.330 --> 10:18.830
Isn't that
a little predatory?

10:18.830 --> 10:20.710
Well, the woman whose
life I'm trying to save

10:20.710 --> 10:22.380
is a military surgeon.

10:22.380 --> 10:25.710
She's saved hundreds of
soldiers' lives. She's a hero.

10:25.710 --> 10:28.420
So I'm okay with you
feeling a little predatory.

10:28.420 --> 10:31.040
And whoever does
find this donor for me

10:31.040 --> 10:32.500
gets to scrub in
on the surgery.

10:32.500 --> 10:35.750
♪ Ooh-ooh, ooh-ooh ♪

10:35.750 --> 10:37.540
It's a good thing.

10:37.540 --> 10:38.830
You want this.

10:38.830 --> 10:40.120
[ Sub-I's murmuring ]

10:40.120 --> 10:42.250
Go!

10:43.670 --> 10:46.000
[ Chuckles ]

10:46.000 --> 10:48.830
[ Woman on P.A.
speaking indistinctly ]

10:51.000 --> 10:53.000
[ Telephone rings ]

10:53.000 --> 10:56.040
Hey, hey. Andrew.

10:56.040 --> 10:57.710
Or is it Andrea?

10:57.710 --> 10:59.250
Andrew, please.

10:59.250 --> 11:01.460
Why is your sister
talking to Bailey?

11:01.460 --> 11:03.540
I don't know. She asked me
to introduce them, so I did.

11:03.540 --> 11:06.170
Well...why?

11:06.170 --> 11:08.420
I-I mean,
what does she do?

11:08.420 --> 11:10.460
For a living.
What's she do for a living?

11:10.460 --> 11:13.250
I see you two did a lot
of talking last night.

11:13.250 --> 11:15.670
She's an OB-GYN.

11:17.080 --> 11:18.880
Huh.

11:18.880 --> 11:21.210
The male brain, in all its
facets and all its states,

11:21.210 --> 11:22.880
has been studied
quite thoroughly,

11:22.880 --> 11:24.500
but nobody has studied
this aspect

11:24.500 --> 11:27.210
of the female anatomy
at all until now.

11:27.210 --> 11:28.830
"This aspect,"
meaning...

11:28.830 --> 11:30.250
The body and the brain,

11:30.250 --> 11:32.710
before, during,
and after orgasm.

11:32.710 --> 11:34.880
As with all
the other organs,

11:34.880 --> 11:36.290
they study the male brain

11:36.290 --> 11:37.580
and they expect
the female brain

11:37.580 --> 11:39.790
to magically fit in
with their conclusions.

11:39.790 --> 11:42.250
But as you and I know,
our bodies are quite different,

11:42.250 --> 11:44.920
so any medications we might need
will also be different.

11:44.920 --> 11:47.460
And your study is funded?

11:47.460 --> 11:49.250
The drug companies
have finally realized

11:49.250 --> 11:50.580
that there is money
to be made

11:50.580 --> 11:53.880
in developing the equivalent
of a female Viagra.

11:53.880 --> 11:55.620
My personal fascination

11:55.620 --> 11:58.250
is with the role
sexual stimulation can play

11:58.250 --> 12:00.290
in pain control for women.

12:00.290 --> 12:02.250
But of course,
nobody will fund that study.

12:02.250 --> 12:04.210
So this way,
two pigeons, one rock.

12:04.210 --> 12:05.710
Uh...

12:05.710 --> 12:09.250
Okay, I understand your
hesitation, Dr. Bailey. I-I do.

12:09.250 --> 12:11.210
But when I heard
my brother was working

12:11.210 --> 12:13.880
for a female
chief of surgery?

12:13.880 --> 12:17.210
Ah, do you know
just how rare that is?

12:17.210 --> 12:18.960
Look, let me just
get this right.

12:18.960 --> 12:21.120
You want me to let you

12:21.120 --> 12:24.420
have women masturbate
in my MRI machine

12:24.420 --> 12:26.710
so that you can study their
brains while they orgasm?

12:26.710 --> 12:28.000
Yes.

12:28.000 --> 12:30.290
-In the interest of science?
-Yes.

12:30.290 --> 12:32.540
[ Inhales sharply ]

12:32.540 --> 12:35.500
♪♪

12:35.500 --> 12:36.670
Done.

12:36.670 --> 12:39.920
♪♪

12:39.920 --> 12:42.750
Well, the good news is you get
a fancy, new grown-up room

12:42.750 --> 12:45.120
while they paint
the peds ward.

12:45.120 --> 12:46.710
David: Is there really
nothing else we can give him?

12:46.710 --> 12:48.080
I mean,
not even an aspirin?

12:48.080 --> 12:49.960
He's maxed out
on opiates.

12:49.960 --> 12:52.790
And just one aspirin will do
nothing for his pain,

12:52.790 --> 12:55.290
but it'll thin his blood
and destroy his chances
of a successful surgery.

12:55.290 --> 12:56.580
You understand?

12:56.580 --> 12:59.540
W-What do I do?
I mean, this is...

12:59.540 --> 13:02.000
Watching my kid in this
much pain, what do I do?

13:02.000 --> 13:04.960
Well, he plays baseball, right?
So what do you tell him?

13:04.960 --> 13:07.290
When it's the ninth inning
and his team is down
and the pressure's on,

13:07.290 --> 13:09.790
you...you say,
"You can do it."

13:09.790 --> 13:12.040
You say, "You got this."

13:13.460 --> 13:15.580
David.

13:15.580 --> 13:18.040
You got this.

13:19.620 --> 13:26.290
♪♪

13:33.830 --> 13:35.460
Jackson: No, no.
She cannot do the surgery.

