I didn't ask for his opinion.
I asked for his help.

13:37.120 --> 13:39.080
He said no. I moved on. And in
case anyone needs reminding,

13:39.080 --> 13:40.710
I am the chief
of neurosurgery!

13:40.710 --> 13:42.670
Good for you, but the
tumor's invading his jaw.

13:42.670 --> 13:44.250
The difficult part of the
surgery is in his face,

13:44.250 --> 13:45.960
not his brain.
You are not an ENT.

13:45.960 --> 13:47.330
It is compressing
his trigeminal nerve.

13:47.330 --> 13:48.710
It is causing
debilitating pain.

13:48.710 --> 13:50.040
And just because
you are afraid of it

13:50.040 --> 13:51.880
doesn't mean
I have to be!

13:51.880 --> 13:55.420
Avery, if she feels
she has it in hand --

13:55.420 --> 13:57.830
Oh, she doesn't. She -- She
does not have it in hand.

13:57.830 --> 14:01.080
It's not your place to
decide that! It's hers!

14:01.080 --> 14:02.710
Her patient,
her decision.

14:02.710 --> 14:05.040
[ Knock on door ]

14:05.040 --> 14:06.790
Sorry to interrupt.

14:06.790 --> 14:09.380
Jackson, I'm doing a total
abdominal-wall transplant,

14:09.380 --> 14:11.170
and I could really use
some help with the nerves

14:11.170 --> 14:12.920
and the vascular
microanastomosis.

14:12.920 --> 14:15.000
An abdominal-wall
transplant?

14:15.000 --> 14:16.540
So you will get on board
with her groundbreaking surgery,

14:16.540 --> 14:17.790
but not mine.

14:17.790 --> 14:19.080
Oh, no, yours
is not groundbreaking.

14:19.080 --> 14:21.040
Yours is
reckless endangerment.

14:23.790 --> 14:25.580
[ Shoes clatter ]

14:25.580 --> 14:28.380
Yes, sir, he's 10 years old.
He's a Syrian refugee.

14:28.380 --> 14:30.540
But, General, if I may,
she was held hostage

14:30.540 --> 14:32.580
for a decade,
and he is her son.

14:32.580 --> 14:34.290
No, he wasn't
legally adopted but --

14:34.290 --> 14:36.170
Is there any way to cut
through some of this red
tape a little faster?

14:36.170 --> 14:38.290
No, not legally, but --
Well, then could you
recommend an attorney

14:38.290 --> 14:39.790
who's better than you?!
Damn it!

14:39.790 --> 14:41.960
-All right, thank you, sir.
-Yes, sir. I'll tell her.

14:41.960 --> 14:43.250
[ Sighs ]

14:43.250 --> 14:45.000
[ Beep ]

14:45.000 --> 14:46.290
No.
[ Phone clatters ]

14:48.790 --> 14:50.830
-This surgery could kill her.
-This surgery is her best shot.

14:50.830 --> 14:52.500
Her best shot is to lay
in that bed and heal.

14:52.500 --> 14:55.420
But she won't.
Megan won't.

14:55.420 --> 14:57.080
She's not gonna lie there
for six months

14:57.080 --> 14:58.460
with her kid over there,
and you know it.

14:58.460 --> 14:59.670
She's going back to Iraq.

14:59.670 --> 15:01.380
And if that wound
gets infected...

15:01.380 --> 15:03.790
Owen, this surgery
is her best option.

15:08.210 --> 15:11.790
♪♪

15:11.790 --> 15:13.620
♪ Oh-oh, yeah ♪

15:13.620 --> 15:15.790
This woman has been dead
three days.

15:15.790 --> 15:18.830
Is that too long?

15:18.830 --> 15:21.960
♪ Oh-oh, ah-ah ♪

15:21.960 --> 15:24.120
Shotgun to the abdomen.

15:24.120 --> 15:26.250
You don't see
a problem here?

15:26.250 --> 15:27.830
You can't repair it?

15:27.830 --> 15:29.710
♪ Better watch
every word on your lips ♪

15:29.710 --> 15:33.580
♪ And, two, don't get too ahead
of yourself, not yet, three ♪

15:33.580 --> 15:36.000
Did I mention
our patient is female?

15:36.000 --> 15:37.500
Yes.

15:37.500 --> 15:39.080
♪ And, number four,
stop asking for it ♪

15:39.080 --> 15:40.790
♪ You get what you get ♪

15:40.790 --> 15:44.210
♪ The birds got the trees,
and the bees got the honey ♪

15:44.210 --> 15:47.880
♪ And your dog days,
they ain't gonna fly ♪

15:47.880 --> 15:49.460
♪ My body, my rules ♪

15:49.460 --> 15:51.170
♪ And tonight I'm kissing you ♪

15:51.170 --> 15:53.120
My party, I choose

15:53.120 --> 15:55.000
♪ Ooh, lucky, lucky you ♪

15:55.000 --> 15:56.620
♪ I break 'em if I wanna ♪

15:56.620 --> 15:58.620
♪ And tonight
I think I'm gonna ♪

15:58.620 --> 15:59.790
Hello.

15:59.790 --> 16:01.710
Do you need the MRI?

16:01.710 --> 16:03.380
-No.
-No.

16:03.380 --> 16:05.210
No. We just heard
about the, um...

16:05.210 --> 16:06.830
My study?

16:06.830 --> 16:08.710
Exactly. Yeah.

16:08.710 --> 16:10.290
I'm Maggie Pierce.

16:10.290 --> 16:11.620
I'm the head of
cardiothoracic surgery.

16:11.620 --> 16:14.250
Maggie Pierce who used to
date my little brother?

16:14.250 --> 16:17.290
-Uh, no, I don't think so.
-Uh, DeLuca.

16:17.290 --> 16:19.920
-What?
-She's DeLuca's sister.

16:19.920 --> 16:22.330
You're even more beautiful than
my stupid little brother said.

16:22.330 --> 16:25.710
I am?! He is? He what?
What did he say?

16:25.710 --> 16:27.250
Whoa! Orgasm!

16:27.250 --> 16:30.210
That is the most active uptake
I have ever seen on an MRI.

16:30.210 --> 16:31.580
It's bright.

16:31.580 --> 16:33.460
I'm always looking
for volunteers

16:33.460 --> 16:36.000
if any of you
have any free time.

16:36.000 --> 16:37.710
No.
No, thank you.

16:37.710 --> 16:39.000
[ Laughter ]

16:39.000 --> 16:40.460
Cool study,
though!

16:40.460 --> 16:42.250
♪ Tonight I'm kissing you ♪

16:42.250 --> 16:43.830
♪ Ooh ♪

16:43.830 --> 16:45.080
Jo boned a Sub-I.

16:45.080 --> 16:46.920
Six -- What?

16:46.920 --> 16:49.120
Yeah, more specifically,
the Sub-I whose glasses...

16:49.120 --> 16:51.420
[ Gasps ] No.
Yes.

16:51.420 --> 16:52.750
She did that
because you told her

16:52.750 --> 16:54.290
about looking up
her husband?

16:54.290 --> 16:56.580
No. I-I didn't tell her
about that.

16:56.580 --> 16:58.580
Oh, well, she did it
because you're avoiding her

16:58.580 --> 17:00.330
because you're too wimpy
to tell her

17:00.330 --> 17:02.000
you looked up
her husband.

17:02.000 --> 17:03.290
Maybe she just did it.

17:03.290 --> 17:04.960
Maybe it doesn't have
anything to do with me.

17:04.960 --> 17:06.710
[ Laughing ] Oh, please!
Jo is so hot.

17:06.710 --> 17:08.710
She could sleep
with anyone she wants.

17:08.710 --> 17:11.380
She chose Glasses? It has
everything to do with you.

17:11.380 --> 17:13.920
When I slept with George, it had
everything to do with Derek.

17:13.920 --> 17:15.500
I still can't believe
you did that.

17:15.500 --> 17:18.920
Okay, we are way too old to
be having this conversation.

17:18.920 --> 17:21.380
Okay, just -- just
tell me why you did it.

17:21.380 --> 17:23.040
Because he was there.

17:23.040 --> 17:24.210
Yeah,
that's not an answer.

17:24.210 --> 17:25.880
Because he wasn't Alex.

17:25.880 --> 17:28.620
Mm, still not quite
an answer.

17:28.620 --> 17:31.080
Because I choose
bad guys, okay?

17:31.080 --> 17:33.750
I choose...
really bad guys.

17:33.750 --> 17:35.040
Violent guys.

17:35.040 --> 17:39.000
In the past, I have chosen
guys who have hurt me.

17:39.000 --> 17:40.380
What?
Like, physically?

17:40.380 --> 17:41.920
Yeah.

17:44.960 --> 17:46.710
If a guy hurts you
physically,

17:46.710 --> 17:49.960
that has nothing to do with you
or who you choose.

17:49.960 --> 17:51.540
That's not your fault.

17:51.540 --> 17:53.040
And I just don't think
Karev is --

17:53.040 --> 17:55.250
I saw him beat Andrew
to a pulp.

17:55.250 --> 17:56.750
I didn't think he had that
in him, either,

17:56.750 --> 17:58.460
and then I watched it.
I --

17:58.460 --> 18:00.500
Well, you have your own
history of volatility.

18:00.500 --> 18:02.290
It's self-defense.
It's different.

18:02.290 --> 18:05.710
Hey, Jo?
I mean, Dr. Wilson.

18:05.710 --> 18:07.880
-Dr. Jo Wilson.
-Yes?

18:07.880 --> 18:08.960
You have a minute?

18:08.960 --> 18:10.000
[ Sighing ] Yeah.

18:11.710 --> 18:13.750
[ Chuckles ]

18:13.750 --> 18:16.250
Levi: She's 35.
Motorcycle accident.

18:16.250 --> 18:18.000
-Wasn't wearing a helmet.
-[ Scoffs ] Stupid.

18:18.000 --> 18:19.170
Right.
So she's brain-dead.

18:19.170 --> 18:21.620
But no injury
to the chest or abdomen.

18:21.620 --> 18:24.120
Name is Shaugnessy,
which sounds pretty Scottish.

18:24.120 --> 18:26.920
Or Irish?
Definitely pale.

18:26.920 --> 18:28.880
I-I think she's
a pretty perfect match.

18:28.880 --> 18:30.330
So what's the problem?

18:30.330 --> 18:32.620
I don't know if it's appropriate
to approach a family

18:32.620 --> 18:34.120
while their grief
is this fresh.

18:34.120 --> 18:35.670
It's not
really appropriate

18:35.670 --> 18:37.250
for you to
approach them at all.

18:37.250 --> 18:38.920
Right. But, I-I mean,

18:38.920 --> 18:40.580
I'd really love to scrub in
on that surgery, so --

18:40.580 --> 18:41.830
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Wait.

18:41.830 --> 18:44.580
If you find the donor,
you get to scrub in?

18:44.580 --> 18:45.880
Page Dr. Grey.

18:45.880 --> 18:48.380
I want to fix it, you know?
I want to turn back time.

18:48.380 --> 18:49.500
I just want to get
everything right.

18:49.500 --> 18:51.000
I want her
to not be captured.

18:51.000 --> 18:53.290
I just want to fix everything.
And Meredith says she can.

18:53.290 --> 18:54.920
Meredith says
she can fix her.

18:54.920 --> 18:56.830
And all I am is terrified
that I'm gonna lose her again.

18:56.830 --> 18:59.120
She doesn't need you
to turn back time, Nathan.

18:59.120 --> 19:00.670
She just needs you
to be with her.

19:00.670 --> 19:02.500
She needs to know that
you're all-in with her.

19:02.500 --> 19:04.670
'Cause anything less than that,
anything in between,

19:04.670 --> 19:06.500
is torture.

19:08.080 --> 19:09.420
What do you got?

19:09.420 --> 19:11.290
35-year-old female, fit,
Caucasian, brain dead.

19:11.290 --> 19:12.920
Family have approved
the donation.

19:12.920 --> 19:15.710
Whew! Do an
infectious-disease screen.

19:15.710 --> 19:16.880
Congratulations, Wilson.

19:16.880 --> 19:19.250
If this checks out,
you get to scrub in.

19:19.250 --> 19:21.790
Thank you, Dr. Grey.
Great job.

19:21.790 --> 19:23.420
Get me a coffee.

19:23.420 --> 19:25.920
[ Woman sobbing ]

19:35.080 --> 19:36.460
But she was mine. I found her.
I trusted you!

19:36.460 --> 19:38.290
It means nothing to you
to scrub in on that surgery.

19:38.290 --> 19:39.330
And after what happened
in my O.R.?

19:39.330 --> 19:41.380
She won't even let you
near the table.

19:41.380 --> 19:43.580
For me, this could be
a game-changer.

19:43.580 --> 19:46.920
That's not an apology!
You owe me an apology!

19:46.920 --> 19:48.250
No, she doesn't
owe you anything.

19:48.250 --> 19:50.290
-Alex, don't.
-She's a senior resident.

19:50.290 --> 19:52.710
You're not even a first year,
which makes you a zero year.

19:52.710 --> 19:54.290
You're a zero that
dropped a foreign object

19:54.290 --> 19:56.170
in the surgical field
of a 7-year-old.

19:56.170 --> 19:57.880
You're only here
because Dr. Wilson

19:57.880 --> 19:59.960
handled your screw-up
and covered your ass.

19:59.960 --> 20:01.960
Got it?!
Yeah. I-I'm a zero.

20:01.960 --> 20:03.040
Okay.

20:05.250 --> 20:07.000
Thank you.

20:07.000 --> 20:08.830
[ Chuckles ]
I'm sorry.

20:08.830 --> 20:10.210
[ Laughing ]
It's -- It's funny.

20:10.210 --> 20:12.790
[ Laughs ]
I can't believe you...

20:12.790 --> 20:15.040
[ Laughing ]

20:15.040 --> 20:17.920
I know! [ Sighs ]

20:17.920 --> 20:20.040
We have to ta--

20:20.040 --> 20:22.960
Hey, so, I had to go to
three different bakeries,
but I found cinnamon cake.

20:22.960 --> 20:24.080
She can't eat.
I know.

20:24.080 --> 20:26.120
But she said she
wanted to smell it, so...

20:26.120 --> 20:27.460
You sent him
on a fool's errand?

20:27.460 --> 20:29.620
I needed some time for us
to all get on the same page.

20:29.620 --> 20:31.750
-What same page?
-Sit down, Owen.

20:31.750 --> 20:34.170
We need
to talk to you.

20:34.170 --> 20:36.580
What about?
About your sham
of a marriage.

20:36.580 --> 20:42.000
♪♪

20:42.000 --> 20:43.080
[ Retching ]
Oh, you got this, buddy.

20:43.080 --> 20:44.380
You got this.

20:44.380 --> 20:46.460
I'm so proud of you.
[ Coughs ]

20:48.500 --> 20:49.920
[ Coughing ]

20:54.420 --> 20:57.330
Dr. Shepherd, are you sure
that this surgery

20:57.330 --> 21:00.000
is the right thing
for Beau?

21:00.000 --> 21:02.790
No one's ever sure
of anything, DeLuca.

21:02.790 --> 21:05.120
Stop trying to be sure.
It's a losing battle.

21:05.120 --> 21:06.420
I-I just --

21:06.420 --> 21:08.670
I feel like you're
adding pain to his pain...

21:08.670 --> 21:10.710
for a surgery that
you're not sure about

21:10.710 --> 21:12.330
on a tumor
that is benign.

21:12.330 --> 21:15.830
Because his pain
is not benign.

21:15.830 --> 21:18.210
You think it's a better
plan to send him home with
no hope and an oxy habit?

21:18.210 --> 21:20.960
He will be a shell
of the kid he once was.

21:20.960 --> 21:24.880
A ghost. An addict.
This pain will waste him.

21:24.880 --> 21:27.080
I will not send that family home
with no hope.

21:27.080 --> 21:28.540
Not when there's a chance
I can fix it.

21:28.540 --> 21:34.000
♪♪

21:34.000 --> 21:35.500
Been thinking
about your thing.

21:35.500 --> 21:37.000
Don't want to.
Can't stop.

21:37.000 --> 21:38.710
[ Gasps ] Can I call you
New Stephanie?

21:38.710 --> 21:40.210
[ Chuckles ] Yeah.

21:40.210 --> 21:42.830
Uh, okay.
Here's my heartfelt advice.

21:42.830 --> 21:44.460
I hear what you're saying,

21:44.460 --> 21:46.670
but I think Karev thought
DeLuca was hurting you.

21:46.670 --> 21:48.790
And I get that you have some
kind of history with bad guys,

21:48.790 --> 21:50.420
but I just don't think
you should feel like

21:50.420 --> 21:52.250
Karev is
that kind of guy.

21:52.250 --> 21:54.580
Uh. No. Oh, no.

21:54.580 --> 21:56.880
You do not get to tell a woman
how she should feel

21:56.880 --> 21:59.120
after she witnesses something
like what she witnessed

21:59.120 --> 22:01.210
between Karev
and DeLuca.

22:01.210 --> 22:03.420
You don't know what it's like
to be female

22:03.420 --> 22:05.500
watching men
assert their authority

22:05.500 --> 22:07.620
by throwing
lethal punches.

22:07.620 --> 22:10.960
You don't get
an opinion on this.

22:10.960 --> 22:13.620
You know...you're right.

22:16.960 --> 22:19.120
You don't have to
listen to anyone on this

22:19.120 --> 22:23.080
because you are a powerful woman
and you know your own mind.

22:24.210 --> 22:26.120
-Thank you, Chief.
-Mm-hmm.

22:28.170 --> 22:31.500
But Karev is a puppy dog.
And he wouldn't hurt a fly.

22:31.500 --> 22:34.500
Unless he thought
that fly was hurting you.

22:34.500 --> 22:41.580
♪♪

22:41.580 --> 22:43.460
-That's not true!
-She's entirely absent.

22:43.460 --> 22:45.580
She said hello to me that first
morning and then she left.

22:45.580 --> 22:46.920
She wanted
to give us space.

22:46.920 --> 22:48.500
That's literally
all she gives you.

22:48.500 --> 22:50.250
And I'm not the only one
that sees it.

22:50.250 --> 22:52.250
You seemed happy
at your wedding mostly,

22:52.250 --> 22:53.790
although she was
awfully late.

22:53.790 --> 22:55.830
Wait! She was late
to the wedding?

22:55.830 --> 22:57.790
-She...panicked.
-And you married her anyway?

22:57.790 --> 22:59.710
Teddy, could you please
explain that marriage

22:59.710 --> 23:02.330
isn't as simple as my sister
would want it to be?

23:02.330 --> 23:03.750
I'm with her, Owen.

23:03.750 --> 23:05.420
You married a patient

23:05.420 --> 23:07.290
because he needed
your medical insurance.

23:07.290 --> 23:08.420
Because he would've
died without it.

23:08.420 --> 23:09.830
-Sounds noble to me.
-It was.

23:09.830 --> 23:11.540
Yeah, and then you
fell in love with him.

23:11.540 --> 23:13.170
-You did?
-Because he was amazing.

23:13.170 --> 23:14.670
Evelyn:
She's not here, Owen.

23:14.670 --> 23:16.710
She's in this hospital.
I see her walking the halls.

23:16.710 --> 23:18.290
But she's not here.

23:18.290 --> 23:19.880
Your family is gathered.

23:19.880 --> 23:21.460
Is she family or not?

23:21.460 --> 23:22.580
I don't need her here.

23:22.580 --> 23:24.670
And you don't see a problem
with that?

23:24.670 --> 23:27.040
[ Scoffs ] Why is your wife
not the person you turn to

23:27.040 --> 23:28.710
for comfort?
Okay! You said it!

23:28.710 --> 23:30.540
Okay? All of you.
And I heard it.

23:30.540 --> 23:33.080
Is that it?
No, that's not it!

23:33.080 --> 23:35.750
Whatever happens
in your stupid marriage...

23:35.750 --> 23:39.380
if I die...

23:39.380 --> 23:41.750
I need you to promise me that
you'll take care of Farouk.

23:41.750 --> 23:43.120
You'll do whatever
you have to do.

23:43.120 --> 23:46.210
You'll move wherever
you have to move.

23:46.210 --> 23:48.210
He is one half of my heart,
and you are the other half,

23:48.210 --> 23:50.170
and I need to know
that you've got him.

23:53.960 --> 23:55.920
-Damn it, Megan.
-What?

23:55.920 --> 23:58.080
I was gonna storm out, and you
just made that really hard!

23:58.080 --> 23:59.750
That was
the whole design!

23:59.750 --> 24:02.460
[ Laughter ]

24:02.460 --> 24:05.420
Ow. Ow. Don't me laugh.
[ Laughing ]

24:05.420 --> 24:08.960
[ Laughing ]
Hey, babe.

24:08.960 --> 24:10.790
Hey.
[ Laughter ]

24:10.790 --> 24:11.920
Are we laughing or crying?

24:11.920 --> 24:13.790
Both.
[ Laughter ]

24:13.790 --> 24:16.460
Well, sorry to be the one
to break up the party,

24:16.460 --> 24:19.460
but I was hoping to get
a little time alone with Megan.

24:21.290 --> 24:24.460
[ Beeping ]

24:24.460 --> 24:26.210
Hey.

24:26.210 --> 24:29.040
Arizona, hi! Come in.
Close the door.

24:35.580 --> 24:38.620
So, um...do you have
a patient in there now?

24:38.620 --> 24:40.580
No.
Just reviewing scans.

24:40.580 --> 24:42.000
Wow!

24:42.000 --> 24:43.880
Right?
Aren't they beautiful?

24:43.880 --> 24:46.250
Yes. Gosh. Wow.
They're so colorful.

24:46.250 --> 24:48.080
Mm-hmm.

24:48.080 --> 24:51.040
And...you see here?

24:51.040 --> 24:53.380
[ Mouse clicking ]

24:53.380 --> 24:55.420
Here's where the
tension's building.

24:58.080 --> 24:59.330
And here...

24:59.330 --> 25:01.500
[ Mouse clicks ]

25:01.500 --> 25:03.500
...a little more tension.

25:03.500 --> 25:05.670
Uh-huh...uh...

25:07.290 --> 25:08.580
And here...

25:08.580 --> 25:10.170
[ Mouse clicks ]

25:13.750 --> 25:16.380
we're building...

25:16.380 --> 25:17.830
toward climax.

25:17.830 --> 25:19.250
Uh-huh.

25:19.250 --> 25:22.460
And here...we have...

25:25.830 --> 25:27.000
...release.

25:27.000 --> 25:29.620
[ Chuckles ] Uh-huh.

25:29.620 --> 25:32.170
Mm-hmm.

25:32.170 --> 25:35.750
The female brain
is a magical place.

25:35.750 --> 25:38.330
[ Exhales sharply ]

25:38.330 --> 25:41.710
[ Laughing ] Ow!

25:41.710 --> 25:43.080
Oh, no!
Mm-hmm.

25:43.080 --> 25:44.290
Do not get down
on that floor.

25:44.290 --> 25:45.920
That is nasty. You do not
need to be down there.

25:45.920 --> 25:47.830
Are you gonna let me
get through this?
Probably not!

25:47.830 --> 25:49.580
Okay, I made a real mess
of this the first time.

25:49.580 --> 25:51.170
So I'd appreciate it
if you'd shut up

25:51.170 --> 25:52.790
and let me get
through it this time.
Okay, I'm sorry.

25:52.790 --> 25:54.080
It's hurting my knees.

25:54.080 --> 25:55.790
Megan Hunt...

25:55.790 --> 25:58.170
[ Laughing, sobbing ]

26:00.250 --> 26:03.080
I have loved you
since the day I met you.

26:03.080 --> 26:06.080
I don't know how I got through
these last 10 years without you.

26:06.080 --> 26:07.960
And now that you're back,
I don't want to spend

26:07.960 --> 26:10.170
one more day without knowing
that you and I have actually --

26:10.170 --> 26:12.420
We have a match, Megan.

26:12.420 --> 26:15.080
Oh.

26:15.080 --> 26:17.330
Whoa. Sorry.

26:17.330 --> 26:19.580
I'm so sorry.

26:19.580 --> 26:21.210
I'm...

26:21.210 --> 26:23.000
No, no, no.
Don't -- Don't be sorry.

26:23.000 --> 26:25.040
I need that flesh to be fresh
when you sew it on me.

26:25.040 --> 26:27.580
We can do this
another time.

26:30.830 --> 26:31.960
Are you ready?

26:34.710 --> 26:37.000
-Are you?
-Absolutely.

26:38.880 --> 26:40.120
Let's do this.

26:48.170 --> 26:52.120
♪♪

26:52.120 --> 26:53.500
Hey.

26:53.500 --> 26:54.670
Hey.

26:54.670 --> 26:56.380
-How's Megan?
-She's gone to surgery.

26:56.380 --> 26:59.040
Amelia, can we talk?
I just need a minute.

27:00.960 --> 27:04.540
[ Sighs ] Amelia, I'm afraid
that something's wrong.

27:04.540 --> 27:06.750
I mean, I know -- I know
you go to your AA meetings

27:06.750 --> 27:08.000
and they seem to help,

27:08.000 --> 27:10.330
but I think
you need something else.

27:10.330 --> 27:14.830
Maybe -- Maybe therapy.
Maybe medication.

27:14.830 --> 27:18.210
I think you still have PTSD
from your brother's death.

27:18.210 --> 27:21.080
I don't know. I don't know
because I'm not a shrink.

27:21.080 --> 27:24.290
But I know
the amazing person you are,

27:24.290 --> 27:27.170
and no one in my life
sees that.

27:27.170 --> 27:29.670
The people who love me
don't see that.

27:29.670 --> 27:33.290
So when I look at you
through their eyes...

27:33.290 --> 27:35.580
[ Sighs ]

27:35.580 --> 27:38.670
...I think something's wrong
and I want to help.

27:43.750 --> 27:46.380
Your sister
doesn't like me...

27:46.380 --> 27:48.380
so I need therapy?

27:48.380 --> 27:51.330
Your friend who is
clearly in love with you

27:51.330 --> 27:53.960
does not like me,
so I need medication?

27:53.960 --> 27:57.330
Your mom, who's with a man
half her age, doesn't like me,

27:57.330 --> 28:01.040
so I need help?

28:01.040 --> 28:03.290
Well, thank you
for the offer.

28:03.290 --> 28:05.830
But I am about to go
perform a medical miracle,

28:05.830 --> 28:09.380
so I kind of
need to focus.

28:09.380 --> 28:10.880
Amelia, I-I...

28:10.880 --> 28:13.750
Oh, and, um, if you want Teddy
as much as she wants you,

28:13.750 --> 28:15.120
you can have her.

28:15.120 --> 28:17.000
Really.
It's no skin off my back.

28:20.500 --> 28:23.120
[ Monitors beeping ]

28:23.120 --> 28:25.420
[ Indistinct conversations ]

28:27.210 --> 28:30.040
Jo: The Sub-I with the
glasses -- he found the donor.

28:30.040 --> 28:31.420
Sorry.

28:31.420 --> 28:33.210
Meredith: If you want to
be a shark, be a shark.

28:33.210 --> 28:35.120
Don't apologize for it.

28:35.120 --> 28:37.330
[ Scrubbing ]

28:37.330 --> 28:38.790
[ Chuckles ]

28:38.790 --> 28:40.960
[ Hael's "Ready" plays ]

28:40.960 --> 28:46.830
♪♪

28:46.830 --> 28:49.330
♪ Ready, set, go ♪

28:49.330 --> 28:51.580
♪ Gas to the fire ♪

28:51.580 --> 28:52.750
Ten blade.

28:52.750 --> 28:54.580
♪ Push a little farther ♪

28:54.580 --> 28:56.500
Ten blade.

28:56.500 --> 28:59.880
♪ Jump a little higher,
fast, not slow ♪

28:59.880 --> 29:02.920
♪ Watch me taking over ♪

29:02.920 --> 29:05.460
♪ Running right beside you ♪

29:05.460 --> 29:08.120
♪ Feel me moving closer ♪

29:08.120 --> 29:10.830
♪ Ooh, I'm ready ♪

29:10.830 --> 29:13.710
♪ Ooh, I'm ready ♪

29:13.710 --> 29:18.880
♪ Ooh, I'm ready now,
ready now, ready now ♪

29:18.880 --> 29:20.920
♪ Ooh, uh-huh ♪

29:20.920 --> 29:23.580
♪ I'm ready ♪

29:23.580 --> 29:26.580
♪ Ooh, uh-huh ♪

29:26.580 --> 29:30.000
♪ I'm ready, I'm ready,
I'm ready right now ♪

29:30.000 --> 29:32.920
♪ I'm, I'm ready, I'm ready ♪

29:32.920 --> 29:35.420
♪ I'm ready right now,
paid my dues ♪

29:35.420 --> 29:37.710
Prep the recipient
for the anastomosis.

29:37.710 --> 29:40.080
♪ Standing in your shadow ♪

29:40.080 --> 29:43.040
♪ Give me all the power ♪

29:43.040 --> 29:45.500
Now, that's what it is.

29:45.500 --> 29:48.540
You came here to find out what
your biological mother was like?

29:48.540 --> 29:50.380
There it is.

29:50.380 --> 29:51.790
♪ Don't let yourself
get jealous ♪

29:51.790 --> 29:53.330
Right there.

29:53.330 --> 29:56.330
♪ It will kill you
if you let it, yeah ♪

29:56.330 --> 29:58.120
♪ Ooh, I'm ready ♪

29:58.120 --> 30:00.040
Do you and Meredith
sit in galleries

30:00.040 --> 30:01.500
and watch me
while I operate

30:01.500 --> 30:03.500
and talk about how much
I'm like Ellis?

30:03.500 --> 30:05.960
'Cause I'm kind of a hotshot
myself, if you haven't noticed.

30:05.960 --> 30:09.580
Top of my class at Yale.
Youngest-ever head of cardio.

30:09.580 --> 30:11.750
When I'm impressed
with you,

30:11.750 --> 30:13.880
I don't immediately
credit Ellis.

30:13.880 --> 30:15.880
♪ I'm ready, I'm ready ♪

30:15.880 --> 30:18.500
I guess I like to take a little
of that credit for myself.

30:18.500 --> 30:21.000
♪ Mmm-mmm ♪

30:21.000 --> 30:23.330
But maybe
I shouldn't.

30:23.330 --> 30:26.620
'Cause after that competitive
rant you just had?

30:26.620 --> 30:27.880
Pure Ellis.

30:27.880 --> 30:29.170
[ Laughs ]

30:29.170 --> 30:31.210
♪ Ooh, I'm ready ♪

30:31.210 --> 30:34.670
♪♪

30:34.670 --> 30:36.460
I'm Stephanie.

30:36.460 --> 30:37.920
[ Chuckles ] What?

30:37.920 --> 30:40.420
Jo's been talking to me today,
confiding in me, and...

30:40.420 --> 30:42.210
I think women keep
each other's secrets

30:42.210 --> 30:44.620
no matter how much unnecessary
drama that may cause.

30:44.620 --> 30:48.830
But I can't, so I'm just
gonna tell you that...

30:48.830 --> 30:50.040
she's afraid of you.

30:50.040 --> 30:52.080
What?

30:52.080 --> 30:53.750
She thinks
you could hurt her.

30:53.750 --> 30:55.540
Not emotionally.

30:55.540 --> 30:57.830
She's afraid that you could
hurt her like you hurt DeLuca.

30:57.830 --> 31:03.460
♪♪

31:03.460 --> 31:06.210
Amelia: Look at that.
You see the mastoid?

31:06.210 --> 31:08.290
It's been completely
destroyed by the tumor.

31:08.290 --> 31:10.210
And the nerve compression.
The pain must've been --

31:10.210 --> 31:13.540
Unbearable.

31:13.540 --> 31:18.250
Okay, DeLuca, I'm gonna need you
to do me a favor.

31:18.250 --> 31:21.290
♪ I'm ready,
I'm ready, I'm ready ♪

31:21.290 --> 31:23.920
♪ I'm ready,
I'm ready, I'm ready ♪

31:23.920 --> 31:25.540
♪ Ooh-ooh, I'm ready ♪

31:25.540 --> 31:27.380
Bailey: Well, hot damn.

31:27.380 --> 31:30.500
Would you look at that?
That is a perfect fit.

31:30.500 --> 31:32.670
♪ I'm ready, ooh ♪

31:32.670 --> 31:34.500
[ Applause ]

31:34.500 --> 31:37.540
♪ I'm ready, I'm ready,
I'm ready right now ♪

31:37.540 --> 31:40.120
♪ Ready, ready, ready, ready ♪

31:40.120 --> 31:42.250
♪ Ready, ready, ready, ready ♪

31:42.250 --> 31:44.790
DeLuca: Dr. Avery? Dr. Shepherd
needs you in O.R. two.

31:44.790 --> 31:46.330
Little busy here, DeLuca.
Uh, yeah, but...

31:46.330 --> 31:47.920
she's got Beau Martinez
on the table.

31:47.920 --> 31:50.290
-And h-his jaw is...
-You've got to be kidding me!

31:50.290 --> 31:52.790
[ Monitor beeping ]

31:52.790 --> 31:54.670
I can't believe you
called me out of a surgery

31:54.670 --> 31:56.830
because you started something
you don't know how to finish.

31:56.830 --> 31:58.540
Well, you said you wouldn't
take his jaw apart.

31:58.540 --> 32:00.210
That's right!
So I took it apart.

32:00.210 --> 32:02.330
I just need you to put it
back together again.

32:02.330 --> 32:05.330
It's a little like LEGOS,
which I was never any good at.

32:05.330 --> 32:07.120
I can't make
this piece fit.

32:14.750 --> 32:19.620
♪♪

32:19.620 --> 32:24.460
♪♪

32:24.460 --> 32:27.380
♪ When you get knocked down
and you've had enough ♪

32:27.380 --> 32:30.250
[ Chuckles ]

32:30.250 --> 32:35.960
♪ Oh, I'll be there
to dust you off ♪

32:35.960 --> 32:39.040
♪ When you don't know
what you're gonna do ♪

32:39.040 --> 32:41.210
My arms are a little weak.

32:41.210 --> 32:42.750
Can you...?
Yeah.

32:42.750 --> 32:45.330
♪ I will look after you ♪

32:47.750 --> 32:49.120
♪ Oooh ♪

32:49.120 --> 32:53.040
[ Exhales sharply ]

32:53.040 --> 32:54.420
You ready?

32:54.420 --> 32:59.250
♪♪

32:59.250 --> 33:03.710
♪ And if you ever
should lose heart ♪

33:03.710 --> 33:07.040
[ Chuckles ]
Oh...wow.

33:07.040 --> 33:11.210
♪♪

33:11.210 --> 33:13.250
Can you give us
a minute?

33:13.250 --> 33:14.920
[ Chuckles ]

33:14.920 --> 33:18.170
♪♪

33:18.170 --> 33:20.040
[ Sighs ]

33:20.040 --> 33:27.420
♪♪

33:27.420 --> 33:29.290
Am I alive?

33:29.290 --> 33:32.210
You are.

33:32.210 --> 33:34.170
-Dad?
-I'm right here, son.

33:34.170 --> 33:35.790
It's not hurting.

33:35.790 --> 33:37.880
[ Laughing ]
It doesn't hurt.

33:37.880 --> 33:40.080
[ Laughs ]

33:40.080 --> 33:42.500
That's great.
That's great. Great.

33:43.880 --> 33:45.670
Wow.
That was incredible.

33:45.670 --> 33:48.830
Right? That smile?
That is why we do what we do.

33:48.830 --> 33:51.540
Nope. That was not bravery
or victory.

33:51.540 --> 33:53.580
That was stupidity.
And you got lucky.

33:53.580 --> 33:55.880
You just can't be wrong,
can you?

33:55.880 --> 33:58.830
DeLuca, why don't we look at
this as a teaching moment, huh?

33:58.830 --> 34:01.420
You saw how she handled that.
You realize how lucky she is

34:01.420 --> 34:02.960
that I'm as good
as I am,

34:02.960 --> 34:05.250
how lucky she is that I didn't
report her to the medical board.

34:05.250 --> 34:06.710
Because this is exactly
the kind of thing

34:06.710 --> 34:08.210
that would prompt them
to reevaluate

34:08.210 --> 34:09.330
her license
to practice medicine.

34:09.330 --> 34:10.790
Do you understand me?

34:10.790 --> 34:12.120
-Yes, sir.
-Good.

34:12.120 --> 34:14.670
You keep it up, and your luck
is gonna run out.

34:18.000 --> 34:19.120
[ Chuckles ]

34:24.460 --> 34:25.920
You should've seen
what Shepherd tried --

34:25.920 --> 34:29.210
Shh.
I just got her down.

34:29.210 --> 34:31.670
[ Sighs ]

34:31.670 --> 34:35.120
So, we gonna talk about
what you said to Maggie or what?

34:35.120 --> 34:36.500
Why?
Why would we do that?

34:36.500 --> 34:37.920
We never talk about
anything that matters.

34:37.920 --> 34:39.460
April, come on.
What -- What is this?

34:39.460 --> 34:41.250
Montana.

34:41.250 --> 34:43.500
We never talked about
what happened in Montana.

34:43.500 --> 34:46.920
Would you like to?
I didn't realize we needed to.

34:46.920 --> 34:49.670
Look, Jackson, I get
that you're really good
at compartmentalizing.

34:49.670 --> 34:51.880
You know, like, I'm your friend,
I'm your person,

34:51.880 --> 34:54.830
I'm Harriet's mom,
and sometimes we have sex

34:54.830 --> 34:56.580
and that's totally okay
with you.

34:56.580 --> 34:58.080
I get it.

34:58.080 --> 35:00.710
It's just that you are
a lot better at it than I am.

35:03.250 --> 35:05.750
Montana actually
caused me pain.

35:05.750 --> 35:07.170
Yeah, I thought I was...

35:07.170 --> 35:08.960
I thought I was good.
I thought it was fine.

35:08.960 --> 35:12.290
But then I spent weeks
wondering what it was.

35:12.290 --> 35:14.330
And if it was nothing,

35:14.330 --> 35:18.710
then it's just,
like, casual sex.

35:20.330 --> 35:23.170
Which, to me is...

35:23.170 --> 35:25.120
[ Sighs ]

35:32.750 --> 35:35.040
I -- [ Sighs ]

35:38.710 --> 35:41.040
It causes me pain,
the way that we're doing this.

35:41.040 --> 35:45.830
♪♪

35:45.830 --> 35:49.080
And I -- I don't -- I think
I probably have to move out.

35:50.620 --> 35:52.170
[ Sighs ]

35:55.460 --> 36:03.790
♪♪

36:03.790 --> 36:05.580
-I can't believe it.
-What?

36:05.580 --> 36:07.460
Megan.
And what Grey did.

36:07.460 --> 36:12.000
I mean, that surgery is
gonna put her on the map.

36:12.000 --> 36:13.250
Did you talk to Amelia?

36:13.250 --> 36:15.580
Yeah.
Didn't go real well.

36:15.580 --> 36:17.080
I'm sorry.

36:17.080 --> 36:19.790
You know she hasn't stayed
at home in months?

36:19.790 --> 36:22.080
A lot of months.

36:22.080 --> 36:23.830
She doesn't touch me.

36:25.580 --> 36:26.960
We don't...

36:29.290 --> 36:31.120
She doesn't want
to be married to me.

36:34.000 --> 36:35.460
She said...

36:39.210 --> 36:41.120
What?
W-What did she say?

36:49.710 --> 36:51.540
[ Breathing heavily ]

36:55.670 --> 36:58.790
Owen.

36:58.790 --> 37:01.210
You -- You're married.

37:01.210 --> 37:03.920
And you...are conflicted.

37:03.920 --> 37:05.830
And you --

37:05.830 --> 37:08.790
You are my favorite human
on the planet.

37:08.790 --> 37:13.710
And if we are meant to be more
in this lifetime,

37:13.710 --> 37:17.500
it can't start with you cheating
on -- on -- on -- on your wife.

37:17.500 --> 37:18.710
She doesn't care.

37:18.710 --> 37:20.710
But I care!
And you care!

37:20.710 --> 37:23.580
And I know you, Owen.

37:23.580 --> 37:25.540
I know your guilt.
I know your shame.

37:25.540 --> 37:27.830
And I know what
it'll do to you, so...

37:27.830 --> 37:30.380
Let me stay your
favorite person for now

37:30.380 --> 37:32.080
and you stay mine, okay?

37:35.670 --> 37:37.790
Okay.

37:37.790 --> 37:40.710
I am s--
I am so sorry. I --

37:40.710 --> 37:42.750
No, no, no.
No. No. No.

37:42.750 --> 37:46.380
No. We are okay.

37:46.380 --> 37:48.120
We are okay.

37:50.920 --> 37:53.750
Dr. DeLuca, you still
looking for volunteers?

37:53.750 --> 37:55.210
Always.

37:55.210 --> 37:56.790
Because I am in the mood
to celebrate.

37:56.790 --> 37:58.170
Okay.

37:58.170 --> 38:00.710
Ooh! Toys!

38:00.710 --> 38:02.000
Purple, I think.

38:02.000 --> 38:04.040
Nope -- hot pink.

38:11.580 --> 38:13.500
[ Chuckles ] You're really
getting rid of all of them, huh?

38:13.500 --> 38:14.790
I don't even want
to look at them.

38:14.790 --> 38:16.080
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Y-Y-You --

38:16.080 --> 38:17.500
What about these?
Y-You getting rid of these, too?

38:17.500 --> 38:19.790
These are the
least comfortable pair.

38:19.790 --> 38:22.710
Only if you try
to stand up in them.

38:22.710 --> 38:24.750
Ooh. [ Laughs ]

38:26.750 --> 38:28.500
[ Laughs ]

38:28.500 --> 38:31.250
You're so...

38:31.250 --> 38:33.000
Come here.
What? What?

38:33.000 --> 38:34.620
Sit down.
These are my shoes.

38:34.620 --> 38:35.620
[ Laughs ]

38:35.620 --> 38:38.000
Hey. Ciao.

38:38.000 --> 38:39.540
[ Both speaking Italian ]

38:44.330 --> 38:46.290
Did you have to come
to the hospital I work at

38:46.290 --> 38:48.250
to have women...
masturbate in the MRI?

38:48.250 --> 38:50.670
You don't think that's
the tiniest bit inappropriate?

38:50.670 --> 38:54.580
No. [ Speaking Italian ]

38:54.580 --> 38:56.830
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Who -- Who is that?

38:56.830 --> 39:00.080
In the MRI. You said
it was a friend of mine?

39:00.080 --> 39:05.170
Meredith: As surgeons,
we try to eliminate pain.

39:05.170 --> 39:09.380
As humans, we just try
like hell to avoid it.

39:09.380 --> 39:10.960
[ Door closes ]

39:10.960 --> 39:12.960
You have a minute?

39:12.960 --> 39:15.120
Did you come
to laugh at me again?

39:15.120 --> 39:17.330
No.

39:17.330 --> 39:20.000
[ Sighs ]

39:20.000 --> 39:21.880
You know,
I-I found your husband.

39:21.880 --> 39:24.790
♪ Ooh-ahh ♪

39:24.790 --> 39:27.920
What?
I hired a guy.
I-I found his name.

39:27.920 --> 39:29.380
I looked him up. And...

39:29.380 --> 39:31.540
And then I went
and found him.

39:31.540 --> 39:33.380
Oh, my God, Alex.

39:33.380 --> 39:34.790
Look. [ Sighs ]

39:34.790 --> 39:36.290
You didn't ask me
to do that,

39:36.290 --> 39:39.420
and you -- you didn't give me
permission to do that,

39:39.420 --> 39:42.710
and it was wrong,
and I-I'm sorry.

39:42.710 --> 39:46.380
And, Jo,
I-I swear to God,

39:46.380 --> 39:50.670
I could never,
ever hurt you.

39:50.670 --> 39:53.830
My dad,
he -- he was like your ex.

39:53.830 --> 39:56.880
I'm not like that, all right?
I'm not like my dad.

39:56.880 --> 39:58.960
I mean, I do --
I do things that are wrong.

39:58.960 --> 40:00.250
I do things
that are stupid.

40:00.250 --> 40:04.000
But...I swear to you...

40:04.000 --> 40:06.540
I would never hurt you.

40:06.540 --> 40:07.750
♪ You're the man I go to ♪

40:07.750 --> 40:11.290
♪ You're the man
I row to, ooh ♪

40:11.290 --> 40:14.170
You saw Paul?
Yeah.

40:14.170 --> 40:16.460
♪ You're the man I go ♪

40:16.460 --> 40:18.250
-And you didn't kill him?
-No.

40:18.250 --> 40:20.120
I mean,
I thought about it.

40:20.120 --> 40:22.620
But I-I-I...
came home instead.

40:22.620 --> 40:26.170
♪♪

40:26.170 --> 40:27.960
Okay.

40:27.960 --> 40:30.500
♪♪

40:30.500 --> 40:34.790
♪ Oh, out in the cold ♪

40:34.790 --> 40:38.040
♪ Under the mud ♪

40:38.040 --> 40:42.420
♪ Savior, rein me in ♪

40:42.420 --> 40:45.790
♪ Don't mind my mad behavior ♪

40:45.790 --> 40:48.960
♪ Ooooh ♪

40:48.960 --> 40:51.540
♪ Out in the cold ♪

40:51.540 --> 40:55.580
♪ Savior, rein me in ♪

40:55.580 --> 40:58.790
When we can't avoid pain,
we try to understand it...

40:58.790 --> 41:02.250
Hey.

41:02.250 --> 41:03.620
Hey.

41:03.620 --> 41:07.330
How's everything
with Megan?

41:07.330 --> 41:09.880
Yeah, she's...

41:09.880 --> 41:13.380
She's perfect. Thank you.
You, um -- You were incredible.

41:13.380 --> 41:15.790
So what are you doing
out here?

41:15.790 --> 41:17.580
Well, um...

41:17.580 --> 41:20.580
♪♪

41:20.580 --> 41:22.920
She doesn't want
to be with me.

41:22.920 --> 41:26.170
She, uh...

41:26.170 --> 41:27.960
She thinks I'm still
in love with you.

41:27.960 --> 41:32.500
♪ Oh, out in the cold ♪

